---
title: Merkle Tree Lifecycle — Sequence Diagram
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Admin
    participant API as Backend
    participant MS as Merkle Service
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant SC as Smart Contract
    participant U as User

    Note over A,U: 1. Voter Tree (Eligibility)
    A->>API: Verify student wallets
    API->>DB: SELECT wallet_addresses
    API->>MS: generateMerkleRoot(wallets)
    note right of MS: leaf = keccak256(address)
    MS-->>API: voterMerkleRoot
    API->>SC: setMerkleRoot(root)
    U->>API: GET /api/voters/proof
    API->>MS: generateMerkleProof()
    API-->>U: proof
    U->>SC: castVote(..., proof)
    SC->>SC: MerkleProof.verify()

    Note over A,U: 2. Identity Tree (Candidate)
    A->>API: Approve identities
    API->>DB: SELECT (address, name, year, gender)
    API->>MS: generateIdentityMerkleRoot()
    note right of MS: leaf = keccak256(address, name, year, gender)
    API->>SC: setIdentityMerkleRoot(root)
    U->>API: GET /api/voters/identity-proof
    U->>SC: registerCandidate(..., proof)
    SC->>SC: MerkleProof.verify()

    Note over A,U: 3. RegCode Tree (Portal)
    A->>API: Generate codes
    API->>DB: INSERT registration_codes
    API->>MS: generateRegCodeMerkleRoot()
    note right of MS: leaf = keccak256(studentId, normalize(code))
    API->>SC: setRegCodeMerkleRoot(root)
    U->>API: GET /api/codes/proof
    U->>SC: verifyRegCode(studentId, code, proof)
    SC-->>U: true / false
